2.3 .c miRNA and RNA files are log-normalized.

  • When performing multivariate analyzes, we want each variable to contribute equally to the analysis. However, the original skcm_rna data is very skewed and quite different from each other. Therefore, the “skcm_rna_data” values here are individually log values scaled. Thus, as seen in boxplots, the graph obtained from log-normalized data has a small and standard scale. In addition, since the amount of difference between the variables was scaled, the ratio of each variable to the analysis was equalized.
boxplot(skcm_rna_data[,2:10])

boxplot(skcm_mir_data[,2:10])

5.4 .d This scatter plot describes the relationship between time to death and IFNG in deceased patients, and the red regression line gives the correlation of the graph.

  • The correlation coefficient (R) is almost 0, indicating that the relationship between these two variables is very weak.
  • A P value of 0.66 means that we cannot reject the null hypothesis.
  • An R2 value of 0.0009 means that only 0.9% of the variation in these variables is explained by the relationship between time to death and IFNG.
  • In summary, there is no significant relationship between the amount of IFNG and survival time.

6.5 .e

# Looking at the last graph, it is seen that there is a positive correlation between the T cell signature and CD8A. That is, as the T cell signature increases, the amount of CD8A also increases. This is an expected result because the alpha chain (which aids in antigen recognition) on the surface of CD8+ killer T cells is produced by the CD8A gene.

6.6 .f

# Looking at the last graph, there is a very low positive correlation between T cell signature and expression levels of macrophage and dendritic cell-specific genes compared to CD8A. One of the reasons for the lower positive correlation may be due to the interaction of macrophage and dendritic cells and T cells in the tumor microenvironment. If the expression of macrophages and dendritic cells is less than expected, we can say that there is an interaction of T cells that renders these cells dysfunctional. As a result of negative interaction with each other, the amount of increase in both may be decreased. If the expression of macrophages and dendritic cells is higher than expected, macrophages may produce something such as cytokines that positively affect the function of T cells. Thus, they can increase the immune response against the tumor as a result of their positive interaction with each other, and the number of both can be increased.

7.5 

# The negative correlation of hsa-miR-155-5p with JARID2 and BACH1 genes is negligible. In this case, it can be said that there is no correlation. This can be interpreted as hsa-miR-155-5p was unable to inhibit the translation of these two genes. Here, it can be interpreted that miR155 has no inhibition interaction with these genes. hsa-miR-155-5p has positive correlation with SOCS1 and INPP5D genes. Thus, this could be interpreted as hsa-miR-155-5p increased rather than inhibited the translation of these two genes. This may be due to the inability of miR-155 to exert its inhibitory effect in immunocompromised conditions such as tumors.
